            {
               "text": "<h3>Prerequisites</h3>The game levels complement the texts available in <i>History Tracers</i>. Therefore, we recommend reading the following texts before starting the activities:</p><p><ul><li><b>Figures:</b> In this level, we compare geometric figures to identify similarities and differences. Recommended texts: <htcite0>, <htcite1>, and <htcite2>.</li><li><b>The person's name is:</b> We explore a common genealogical error: the belief in a universal pattern for naming children throughout history. Recommended texts: <htcite3>, and <htcite4>.</li><li><b>Defamations:</b> During the Paulista Civil War, we analyze how the Camargo family sought to incite the population against their enemies. Recommended text: <htcite5>.</li><li><b>The Discoverer:</b> We examine different perspectives on the discovery of the American continent. Recommended texts: <htcite6> y <htcite7>.</li></ul></p>",
